164
00:06:54,619 --> 00:06:57,820
how that he speaks of the reality of His resurrection.

165
00:06:57,820 --> 00:07:00,880
He says that He was seen of Cephas, and then of the twelve.

166
00:07:00,880 --> 00:07:02,619
And then he says this in verse number six,

167
00:07:02,619 --> 00:07:07,619
that He was seen of above 500 brethren at once.

168
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:10,760
And he says of that group of people that many of them,

169
00:07:10,760 --> 00:07:14,059
of whom the greater part remain under this present.

170
00:07:14,059 --> 00:07:15,459
In other words, they were still alive.

171
00:07:16,279 --> 00:07:17,720
They had not yet died.

172
00:07:17,720 --> 00:07:19,220
He does say at the end of the verse

173
00:07:19,220 --> 00:07:21,019
that some are fallen asleep, some have died.

174
00:07:21,019 --> 00:07:23,459
But many of that group, that 500,

175
00:07:23,459 --> 00:07:26,519
they still were alive at the time of the writing

176
00:07:26,519 --> 00:07:28,859
of 1 Corinthians chapter number 15.

177
00:07:28,859 --> 00:07:30,459
We find that you continue,

178
00:07:30,459 --> 00:07:32,839
and he speaks about James and the apostles.

179
00:07:32,839 --> 00:07:36,339
But then Paul says this of himself in verse number eight.

180
00:07:36,339 --> 00:07:39,380
And last of all, He was seen of me also

181
00:07:39,380 --> 00:07:42,279
as of one born out of due time.

182
00:07:42,299 --> 00:07:45,799
And I can understand that Paul is writing no doubt

183
00:07:45,799 --> 00:07:48,739
about that experience as it's recorded in Acts nine.

