00:08:09,200 --> 00:08:12,200
Notice in the first few verses of our text of scripture,

193
00:08:13,019 --> 00:08:14,920
the apostle Paul makes no bones about it.

194
00:08:14,920 --> 00:08:16,640
He says to these believers,

195
00:08:16,640 --> 00:08:20,679
he says, I declared unto you the gospel.

196
00:08:20,679 --> 00:08:23,359
He speaks about the way in which he came to them

197
00:08:23,359 --> 00:08:24,799
and he preached unto them,

198
00:08:24,799 --> 00:08:26,380
and he preached to them the gospel.

199
00:08:26,380 --> 00:08:28,179
What is the gospel?

200
00:08:28,179 --> 00:08:30,359
The reality is that if there's no resurrection,

201
00:08:30,359 --> 00:08:31,700
there's no gospel.

202
00:08:31,700 --> 00:08:35,080
Because the reality is that the gospel in its entirety

203
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:37,760
is not simply the death of Jesus Christ

204
00:08:37,760 --> 00:08:39,080
on the cross of Calvary,

205
00:08:39,080 --> 00:08:42,039
nor is it just simply His death and His burial,

206
00:08:42,880 --> 00:08:45,520
but it is the death, burial, and resurrection

207
00:08:45,520 --> 00:08:47,760
of Jesus Christ that is the gospel.

208
00:08:47,760 --> 00:08:50,440
It is the good news of Jesus Christ.

209
00:08:50,440 --> 00:08:51,799
And we understand this morning,

210
00:08:51,799 --> 00:08:53,119
as we think about the gospel,

211
00:08:53,119 --> 00:08:55,200
that Paul, as he's speaking here,

212
00:08:55,200 --> 00:08:57,320
he says to them in verse number three,

213
00:08:57,320 --> 00:08:59,419
for I delivered unto you, first of all,

214
00:08:59,419 --> 00:09:00,919
that which I also received.

215
00:09:00,919 --> 00:09:04,200
Understand that Paul says, this is not my gospel.

216
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:05,940
If you were to read the book of Galatians

217
00:09:05,940 --> 00:09:08,239
in the first chapter, you would find that Paul

218
00:09:08,239 --> 00:09:10,640
makes it very clear that he is preaching

219
00:09:10,640 --> 00:09:12,479
that which the Lord Jesus Christ

220
00:09:12,479 --> 00:09:15,000
had delivered to him and given him.

221
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:18,119
In fact, he says this in Galatians one,

222
00:09:18,119 --> 00:09:19,919
in verse number 11 and 12,

223
00:09:19,919 --> 00:09:21,719
but I certify you, brethren,

224
00:09:21,719 --> 00:09:23,900
that the gospel which was preached of me

225
00:09:23,900 --> 00:09:27,840
is not after man, for I neither received it of man,

226
00:09:27,840 --> 00:09:29,440
neither was I taught it,

227
00:09:29,440 --> 00:09:32,799
but by the revelation of Jesus Christ.

228
00:09:32,799 --> 00:09:35,799
And so Paul, as he's speaking here in 1 Corinthians 15

229
00:09:35,799 --> 00:09:37,880
to these believers that had been influenced

230
00:09:37,880 --> 00:09:39,840
by these false teachers, he says,

231
00:09:39,840 --> 00:09:42,380
I want to remind you that I came in

232
00:09:42,380 --> 00:09:43,440
and I preached to you.

233
00:09:43,440 --> 00:09:45,320
I delivered unto you, first of all,

234
00:09:45,320 --> 00:09:47,320
that which I also received,

235
00:09:47,320 --> 00:09:51,640
how that Christ died for our sins,

236
00:09:51,640 --> 00:09:53,320
according to the scriptures.

237
00:09:53,320 --> 00:09:55,479
Let me say a few things about verse number three.

238
00:09:55,479 --> 00:09:59,080
It's not just sufficient to say that Jesus died.

239
00:09:59,080 --> 00:10:00,159
There was a reason.

240
00:10:00,159 --> 00:10:06,799
And that reason is given to us in this verse of Scripture throughout the whole of God's

241
00:10:06,799 --> 00:10:07,799
Word.

242
00:10:07,799 --> 00:10:12,919
We find that the reason that Christ died is for our sins.

243
00:10:12,919 --> 00:10:17,599
The Bible says how that Christ died for our sins.

244
00:10:17,599 --> 00:10:19,919
Just grasp that just for a moment this morning.

245
00:10:19,919 --> 00:10:23,739
A couple of weeks ago, we had a missionary last week, but two weeks ago I preached a

246
00:10:23,739 --> 00:10:30,019
message on the sufferings of Jesus Christ and how that Peter said that he was a witness

247
00:10:30,019 --> 00:10:32,959
of the sufferings of Christ.

248
00:10:32,959 --> 00:10:35,719
And we understand this morning that he died for our sins.

249
00:10:35,719 --> 00:10:42,279
You know that sin is a universal condition of mankind?

250
00:10:42,279 --> 00:10:46,279
